			<abstract>
				<p>Benjamin Lewin describes his fate after being deported from the Terezín Ghetto in autumn 1944 until the liberation of the Belzig camp. His is a survivor of various camps. From Auschwitz-Birkenau, he was transported to the Čechovice/Czechowice (Silesia), Gross-Rosen, Buchenwald,
					and Halberstadt labor camps. Lewin briefly describes the living conditions in these camps.</p>
			</abstract>
